bio.experienceSummary:
Hello guardians! My name is Eliyana, and I'm so glad to be here. I'm a marketing and events director living in Manhattan currently, looking to find the perfect family to help out in NYC! I'm down to earth, generous, but not too passive! I make sure to instill wisdom and love into my peers every chance I get. 

I naturally love to teach, nurture and have fun with children. It truly is a gift to engage with kids and see the world through their eyes. I've always been drawn to the wonder and whimsy of our young friends. 

Please ask me any question; I'd love to answer all!

I'm an experienced educator and childcare provider with a passion for helping children grow and thrive. I love fostering creativity, playfulness, and activity and supporting children in their interests. With over a decade of experience, I have had the privilege of caring for kids of all ages, as a full-time nanny, au pair abroad, and babysitter. I also hold a Masters in Teaching and have several years of experience in K-12 classrooms. 

I'm comfortable enforcing household rules and routines, and I always keep parents informed about their child's day and any issues that arise. I'm also happy to help with meal preparation, housekeeping, homework, and taking children to activities outside of the home.

I've completed First Aid and CPR certification programs, taken coursework in early childhood development, and I have worked as a lifeguard and children's swim coach. I'm fluent in English and conversational in French.

description.originalText: Stephanie took great care of our two young kids for an evening while we were visiting NYC. Our 4 year old was raving about how much fun they had together. We would not hesitate to hire Stephanie again.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! My name is Hannah. I am a 26-year-old pre-med student looking for a part-time job nannying or babysitting! I love children and grew up taking care of my younger family members and neighborhood children. I have my CPR and EMT certifications and a previous history working as a tutor, long-term babysitter, private-lesson lacrosse coach, adaptive ski instructor to disabled children, EMT, medical assistant, and lifeguard. My previous employers describe me as extremely outgoing, lighthearted, empathetic, hard-working, and lots of fun. I am extremely active and love playing games both indoors and outdoors and never lack the energy to keep up with young kids. I currently work as a medical and research associate for a Board-Certified Dermatologist. My hours are Monday-Friday 8:30-5:30. I am happy to pick up any shifts outside of those hours. If you have any questions feel free to reach out!

I've been babysitting for most of my life & I love it! I grew up in Hawaii where I regularly babysat for many local families as well as occasionally tourists visiting at hotels. My mom was a Waldorf kindergarten teacher so I started babysitting very early on through connections at the school.

I moved to Boston for college & continued babysitting for various families, often getting recommended to others. I've had several families whose children I've taken care of every week for 7-10 years & watched the kids grow from infants/toddlers to teens.

I also ran my own children's camp where I had anywhere from 4-10 kids. I planned games, treasure hunts, arts & crafts & provided lunch & snacks.

I also do quite a bit of pet sitting. I love animals & always make sure the house is kept as clean & put together as possible. 

Having worked with so many different children & pets over the years I can confidently say I have the experience for whatever you may need. And I'll always make it fun :)

description.originalText: Hiring Miranda is like finding Mary Poppins. Miranda is responsible, dedicated, caring and competent. AND she is amazing with kids. From playing imaginative games to getting them outdoors, to art and music and projects and silliness my kiddos loved her. She managed a household with three kids including a newborn and an elderly dog. She taught my eldest piano and spent hours crafting and doing art projects with my middle. Her presence with the kids was joyful and they loved having her in their lives. Miranda is creative and energetic and also a fantastic communicator and employee. She spent several years with us in various capacities and we could not have been happier with her care for our kiddos, our pet, and our family!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there! I am an Art Therapy graduate student at Pratt Institute with nearly 10 years of childcare experience. Before going back to school I worked as a full-time nanny for a family in Brooklyn who I remain close to. I traveled internationally many times with this family starting when their daughter was only 8 months old. 
Before full-time nannying, I was a preschool teacher and working actor. In undergrad, I wrote and performed for children in several Theater for the Very Young productions (focusing on children under 5 years old). 
I have a deep passion for all creative arts, and my portfolio spans acrylic paint, oil pastel, charcoal, clay, ukulele, found sculpture, jewelry making, embroidery, crochet, needle felting, and whatever other materials I can get my hands on! 

I am currently on school break until the end of January.

description.originalText: Claire did a great job looking after our 20 month old son. He was immediately comfortable with her and seemed to enjoy himself.

bio.experienceSummary: I was raised in a bilingual household. I have both an older and younger sibling. I have been babysitting, tutoring, and teaching since I was a preteen. I have a graduate background in Early Childhood and Human Services. I love youth and I learn so much from them. I love to teach them and enrich their lives. I have been a caregiver for the disabled. My particular connection is personal since I was raised with a blind uncle and another who has been wheelchair bound for nearly 40 years. I have also cared for children with special needs. I am an empathetic person who is a passionate advocate for the rights of others. I am also affiliated with NAMI as well as Neighborhood Cats and ARC certified in Pet First Aid. I am also a NYCDOH licensed animal handier. Feel free to contact me. I hope to hear from you soon.

description.originalText: Ana was prompt, knowledgeable, and caring throughout the year and a half that she worked with my household! I have a needy elderly cat with complex medication needs. She came twice daily to feed, medicate, and clean his environment when I took long international trips (sometimes as long as 3 weeks).

bio.experienceSummary: I am a 23-year-old living in NYC looking for part-time babysitting opportunities! I graduated from Lehigh University as a Division 1 athlete with a major in Psychology and Health in 2023, and I currently work in Marketing. I have 9+ years of babysitting experience with children of all ages, and I love to plan fun activities and cook healthy meals. I am available every weeknight after 5:30pm, as well as weekends. Feel free to reach out any time!

description.originalText: Sophie was prompt, sweet and nurturing with our 14 month old daughter! We would absolutely hire her again to babysit!

bio.experienceSummary:
I love kids and have years of experience with all age ranges, as I babysat for many summers. I was also a volunteer Emergency Medical Technician in college. I am looking to fill some time during gardening leave, before my next role starts mid-summer. Please reach out if you have any questions and I'm looking forward to meeting you! 

Please note, I require introductory calls before confirming any babysitting gigs. I have a flat $100 rate for overnights and every waking hour is billed hourly.

**Experienced Childcare Professional with 5+ Years of Expertise in the city**

I am a professional childcare provider with over five years of experience working with infants, toddlers, and school-aged children. Along with my childcare expertise, I am a professional chef, specializing in creating nutritious, customized meals for children. I am bilingual I'm also good at teaching if you would like to teach them, proficient in managing daily routines, and certified in CPR and First Aid.

I am known for being caring, reliable, and loving. I have a passion for supporting children's growth, creativity, and learning. I am seeking a long-term position where I can be respected, valued, and continue to grow both personally and professionally.

description.originalText: It’s a really helpful person for all what you need. It’s lovely with kids and responsible

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I'm Rebecca and I currently work full-time in Early Intervention supporting children ages birth-3 who have a developmental delay. I am relocating to the East Village to work as a preschool teacher. I have nannied full-time for families in the past and have plenty of experience working with kids. I graduated from Loyola University Chicago with a BS in Human Services, and taught preschool in Greece for a year. I am comfortable working with kids of all ages and abilities, and am CPR and First Aid Certified. I am currently looking for week-night or weekend babysitting or pet sitting opportunities.
